{
  "name": "RPlog_Headed_for_Hijarna",
  "title": "Passage to Hijarna Aboard the Comet's Tail",
  "summary": "Archaeologist Paul Nighman and his companion Ylsa arrive at Coronet Space Port to board the battered freighter Comet's Tail, captained by the Rodian Leebo and crewed by Terrin and Fulk, for a voyage to the world of Hijarna. After settling their few belongings and a tender private moment between Paul and Ylsa, the ship departs. During the hours-long flight, Paul unwraps a gleaming gold-foiled goddess statue, several thousand years old, which captivates Terrin and rouses the normally taciturn, gun-toting Fulk's curiosity. Paul explains his xenoarchaeological quest to recover a set of such relics tied to a millennia-old holy war and the legend of Tamis, having traded the promise of a map to Leebo in exchange for passage. The log is a quiet character and exposition piece establishing the expedition's purpose and crew dynamics, ending with Terrin lost in admiration of the statue.",
